title: San Leandro: Four shot outside Club Caliente night club
content:
SAN LEANDRO — Four people were shot and hospitalized early Monday morning after gunfire broke out in the parking lot of a dance club.
The shooting occurred around 1:55 a.m. in the parking lot of Club Caliente, located in 14600 block of E. 14th Street, San Leandro police Lt. Robert McManus said in a statement. Police were investigating what may have led to the shooting.
The four people hit by the gunfire all were expected to survive, McManus said. They all were taken by ambulance to various hospitals for treatment, McManus said.
Police have not made any arrest, nor have they identified any suspects. Detectives were at the scene Monday morning investigating.
Check back for updates.
